<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>Written evidence submitted by The Royal Society (RaD0013)</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Pro 45 Light'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence submitted by </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">The Royal Society</span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold"> (RaD0013)</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The Royal Society has read with interest the recent report commissioned by the Science and Technology Committee from the National Audit Office. The Society was very happy to discuss this report with the NAO as they were preparing it, and are pleased to see it now in publication.</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The NAO report provides a useful refresh to data and observations that the Society has itself used in its analysis of the UK research landscape, particularly in our 2010 report, </span><a href="http://royalsociety.org/policy/publications/2010/scientific-century/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">The Scientific Century</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">In that report, the Royal Society recommended that the UK should prioritise investment in ‘scientific capital’ – infrastructure, skills and people - with a view to ensuring that the UK ‘remain at the vanguard of international science.’ More recently the Royal Society has worked with the other UK National Academies to reiterate the importance of a long term strategy and investment framework for research and innovation in the UK in our recent joint statement </span><a href="http://royalsociety.org/policy/publications/2013/fuelling-prosperity/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic; text-decoration:underline">Fuelling Prosperity</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">.</span><a name="_ftnref2"></a><a href="#_ftn2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> This would further strengthen the UK’s globally strong position in research and allow us to reap the benefits of research for the economy and society.</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The NAO report offers an overview of the variety of sources of funding for UK research (particularly figures 2, 5 and 6). This diversity of funding provides underpinning strength to UK research, with the streams of public, business, philanthropic and overseas funding complementing each other rather than necessarily overlapping. The Royal Society would be interested to see an in-depth analysis of the interplay between these funding streams, and the levels of funding that is levered between sectors.</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">Other key issues which are particularly striking in the report, and that the Royal Society is also interested in include:</span></p><ul type="disc" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.31pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The relatively low investment by industry in UK R&amp;D (in comparison to our closest overseas competitors – this is also seen in the </span><a href="http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/news/east-asia-leads-the-world-in-business-funding/2006387.article"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; text-decoration:underline">recent report by THE</span></a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt"> on the R&amp;D funding universities attract from business</span><a name="_ftnref3"></a><a href="#_ftn3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">);</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.31pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The concentration of spending in location and sector – specifically pharma and the South East;</span></li><li style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:11pt; line-height:14pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 30.31pt; padding-left:7.94pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">The value of European Union funding to the UK (the Royal Society’s joint submission with the other national Academies to the recent BIS review of the balance of competences between the UK and EU in R&amp;D considers this).</span></li></ul><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">If the UK is to capitalise on its demonstrably excellent research base, it is vital that we understand both the funding and policy landscapes not only in the UK, but also those of our closest competitors. The Royal Society would be keen to discuss any of the points emerging from this report, or other issues relating to the health of the UK research base with you and your Committee. We look forward to working closely with you, and offering any assistance that we can.</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">August 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Pro 45 Light'; font-size:10pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Pro 45 Light'; font-size:6.67pt; vertical-align:super"> </span><a href="http://royalsociety.org/policy/publications/2010/scientific-century/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Pro 45 Light'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://royalsociety.org/policy/publications/2010/scientific-century/</span></a></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn2"></a><a href="#_ftnref2">[2]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Pro 45 Light'; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://royalsociety.org/policy/publications/2013/fuelling-prosperity/"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Pro 45 Light'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://royalsociety.org/policy/publications/2013/fuelling-prosperity/</span></a></p><p style="line-height:14pt; margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn3"></a><a href="#_ftnref3">[3]</a><span style="font-family:'Frutiger LT Pro 45 Light'; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/news/east-asia-leads-the-world-in-business-funding/2006387.article"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Frutiger LT Pro 45 Light'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.timeshighereducation.co.uk/news/east-asia-leads-the-world-in-business-funding/2006387.article</span></a></p></body></html>